{
  "texts": [
    "In each bar chart, the title represents the knowledge generator model (Llama 2: 7B, 13B and 70B).",
    "The x-axis shows different explanation generator models, and the varying few-shot settings (zero-shot, one-shot, two-shot and four-shot) are indicated by different colors in the legend not always strictly linear.",
    "Larger models, such as Llama 2 70B, show steady improvements with more examples, especially in the four-shot setting.",
    "For Llama 2 7B, the improvement from zero-shot to one-shot is smaller compared to the 13B and 70B models, suggesting that the smaller model size is less sensitive to one-shot prompting in this task.",
    "However, by the time we reach the four-shot setting, most models exhibit comparable performance gains, indicating that the four-shot examples allow the models to generate explanations that are more accurate.Figure 5b shows the results of the CSE dataset."
  ]
}